Once your squad is full, new Pikmin will be placed on standby.
New Pikmin will be added to your squad as space opens up. To keep a certain Pikmin in your squad, make sure to mark it as a favorite.
As you gain levels, the number of Pikmin you can have in your squad goes up. Keep leveling up to walk with lots of Pikmin!
In addition to gathering your Pikmin, you can also use your whistle to manage your squad.
Try double-tapping the whistle. Your squad will automatically organize themselves.
Practice using your whistle to give your Pikmin directions!
When you're Flower Planting, you will grow flowers around you as you walk.
While you're planting flowers, petals you've collected from your Pikmin will be used up, one by one.
Flowers will be planted even while the app is closed, and they'll stop when you run out. You can also stop planting at any time.
Other users will be able to see the flowers you plant, so you can cover the world in flowers together!
The more flowers you plant while in Flower Planting mode, the faster the seedlings in your Planter Pack will grow.
On top of earning more points from each step, you'll also be able to grow seedlings faster while you're planting flowers.
When you plant flowers with others, other players can appear on your screen. Have fun planting together!
With Pikmin and people working together, the whole planet could be covered with flowers!

If a Pikmin blooms too many flowers in one day, it will get tired and be unable to grow more.
Bare Pikmin are too tired to eat nectar or go on expeditions—but there's no need to worry!
Pikmin will regrow their leaves each morning, and will be refreshed and ready to explore! But they'll have to rest until then.

You may be wondering what exactly a Pikmin is...
Pikmin are small creatures that look a little like animals and a little like plants.
There are Pikmin all over, but many are asleep and have changed into their seedling forms.
These sleeping Pikmin need your help to wake up.
As a first step, try touching the seedlings.
Pikmin can be grown using special backpacks called Planter Packs.
First, we'll have to plant the seedlings you picked up.
Let's plant the other seedling too.
Now the seedlings you planted will grow as you walk around.
Each step you take will add to the growth of the seedlings.
Try it out! Just walk 10 steps...
See? Your steps made the seedlings grow!
Looks like they're ready to be plucked...
Now let's pluck the other one too.
Next, tap and hold the whistle to gather your Pikmin.
Hey! Looks like they have something for you!
Looks like they want you to take it.
You got nectar from the fruit! Seems like it'd make a good Pikmin snack...
What happens if you tap them?
Pikmin petals have curious properties... Let's hang on to them!
Nice to meet you, %s. The Pikmin can't wait to walk with you!
The more seedlings you grow and the more Pikmin you have, the more fun your walks will be!
Let's plant the seedling you got in your Planter Pack!
It looks like this seedling will take 1,000 steps to grow.
Why not go out and about to grow what you've planted—and maybe find some more seedlings too!
Players who are planting flowers with others will be able to see each other on screen.
Congratulations! You found a Decor Pikmin!
Decor Pikmin are a bit rarer than other types... They wear stuff from around where their seedling was discovered.
You can easily see what varieties of Decor Pikmin you've found by tapping the related badge in your profile.
Postcards include a commemorative photo of something your Pikmin found interesting while out and about.
Each postcard is special and features the Pikmin who were sent out on the expedition. By sure to cherish it!
During your daily lookback, you can earn rewards based on your step count and see an animation showing where you walked.
Your Pikmin may also choose one of the pictures you took that day. If you like, you can keep it on your Lifelog.
If you want Pikmin to look for pictures, they'll need access to your photo library, so grant them permission if you'd like their help!
Even if you close the app, you can inform such as seedlings of growth if there is a push notification.

Step Tanks are useful items that store energy from your steps as you carry them.
When you've taken 1,000 steps with one, you can use it to grow a seedling in your Planter Pack.
You can get Step Tanks from the in-game shop. Use them to grow lots of Pikmin!
You can join other players with Flower Planting with Others mode and plant flowers together!
When Pikmin return from an expedition, they'll sometimes bring a postcard back.
After 9:00 p.m. each day, you'll be able to view your daily lookback!
Background location tracking is disabled on device, so you won't be able to use features that require it to be on.
As you play PikminApp, your level will eventually go up.
As your level goes up, so does the number of Pikmin you can have in your squad, allowing you to keep more Pikmin with you.
To raise your level, you'll need to earn step points, which you'll get by walking and planting flowers!
For more information on your level and step points, check out your in-game profile.
Good work! Your Pikmin have gathered together.
Hmm... Looks like they have an idea.
When you walk around with Pikmin, they'll sometimes find fruit and pick it up.
This is the home screen. You can check the record of your walks with Pikmin here. There are all sorts of other features, so be sure to try them out!
We're all set! Now let's go walk and grow some Pikmin!

Tap it to ask your Pikmin to go collect it for you.
You can collect the item by whistling for your Pikmin once they get back. All you have to do is wait!

column3: Please review the Niantic Privacy Policy for information about how we process your personal data.
PikminApp uses the number of steps you take as part of the game.
Google Fit will be used to count your steps.
When you achieve certain goals in PikminApp, you'll be presented with a badge as proof.
The badges you've earned will be shown in your profile. You can check when you earned each badge by tapping on its icon.
Each badge has various ranks. The higher the rank, the harder it is to earn. Some are quite challenging, but you can do it!
When you interact with your Pikmin, you'll gain Friendship Level with them, which is displayed as a series of hearts.
As your Friendship Level with a Pikmin increases, that Pikmin will be able to produce more flowers each day.
The number of hearts can be increased up to four for each Pikmin. When you reach that level of friendship, the Pikmin may give you something special!
Be sure to keep an eye on your Friendship Level!
It looks like this seedling will take 1,000 steps to grow.
It looks like your Pikmin have picked up a new seedling! Let's plant it in your Planter Pack.
Your Pikmin will always stick by you—or by your feet, at least.
After you've grown and plucked a Pikmin, you can interact with them to your heart's content.
All the Pikmin walking with you will be gone!
By visiting different locations, you can discover a variety of Decor Pikmin!
Your Mii and location will be visible to others, so please keep the planting to safe public spaces.
